CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 6, 1954, pg. 20 reads: "At IKS Teen-Age Open House - A large group of youngsters turned out for the open house program held last week at Irene Kaufmann Settlement and no wonder, for many of their friends were on the bill to entertain them. Among the entertainers was Victor Hereford and his dancing group from Howe Studios.  Mr. Hereford is shown in left bottom photo... - Harris and Moseley Photos."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of dancer Victor Hereford wearing light colored pants, jumping in corner of room in Irene Kaufmann Settlement
